The U.S. economy is experiencing positive growth and job gains. The manufacturing sector has been performing well under President Trump, adding 22,000 jobs in March and a total of 232,000 jobs over the past year. The country's economic growth in the fourth quarter of 2017 was revised up to a solid 2.9 percent annual rate, marking the fastest growth in over a decade. Additionally, the number of people receiving unemployment benefits has reached a 44-year low, and small businesses are raising pay at the highest rate in 17 years. Consumer sentiment is also at a 14-year high, driven by optimism among low-income earners. Finally, U.S. investor optimism remains strong and stable, reaching the highest levels in 17 years.